<recipe>
<title>
Chocolate-Dipped Cookie Dough Bites
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
COOKIE DOUGH
1/2 c . butter room temperature
1/2 c . granulated sugar
1/2 c . brown sugar packed
1 T . vanilla extract
1 c . all-purpose flour
1/2 tsp . kosher salt
1/2 tsp . baking soda
</ingredients>
<instructions>
For the cookie dough, beat together butter and sugars until well-combined.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour, salt, and baking soda, and stir until just combined. Set aside.
For the chocolate, melt together chocolate and coconut oil in microwave. Stir every 30 seconds until chocolate is melted.
To assemble, place one heaping tablespoon of cookie dough on each of half of the crackers.
Top cookie dough with other cracker, and press gently.
Dip cookie dough sandwich into melted chocolate.
Place dipped cookie dough bites on waxed or parchment paper.
Sprinkle with fleur de se, chopped nuts, or other desired toppingl, if using.
Enjoy!
</instructions>
</recipe>
